      "writtenOn": "2017-09-27T18:07:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "IIUC, we run tests in rounds, ie. trigger N tests, wait for all of them to finish, then trigger the ones for which we need more data and wait for those to finish, and repeat until we have enough data or hit the maximum number of attempts.\n\nIf that\u0027s true, then the usage pattern of this class is essentially:\n\nrunner \u003d ThreadRunner()\nwhile not done:\n  for test in tests_to_run:\n    runner.add(test)\n  runner.wait()\n\nI think this class could be simplified if we did this instead:\n\nwhile not done:\n  runner \u003d ThreadRunner()\n  for test in tests_to_run:\n    runner.add(test)\n  runner.wait()\n\nThen we wouldn\u0027t need self.waitCnt or currentWait, and we wouldn\u0027t need a global threadRunner instance; we\u0027d just pass one into run().",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 122,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 122,
        "endChar": 72
      },
      "revId": "6a7f186018f99dd12359f11a4f0188a382ccb540",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
